    <statement><p>Multiply: <m>\displaystyle{ \frac{7}{11} \cdot \frac{3}{14} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{3}{22}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To multiply two fractions, usually we simply multiply both numerators and both denominators. However, it<rsq/>s easier to reduce fractions before multiplying:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   \frac{7}{11} \cdot \frac{3}{14}
           \amp = \frac{7 \cdot 3}{11 \cdot 14} \\
           \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 3}{11 \cdot 2} \\
           \amp = \frac{3}{22}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The answer to this question is <m>\displaystyle{\frac{3}{22}}</m>.</p>
<p>Note that we divided the first numerator and the second denominator by <m>7</m>.</p>
</solution>
